Add a `src/linkedList.js` Doubly Linked List data structure module with the following:

1) `createLinkedList()` - factory function with no arguments.

2) Returns an object with:
   - `append(value)` - add node to end of list.
   - `prepend(value)` - add node to beginning of list.
   - `insertAt(index, value)` - insert value at specific index. Returns true if inserted, false if invalid index.
   - `remove(value)` - remove first occurrence of value. Returns true if removed, false if not found.
   - `removeAt(index)` - remove node at index. Returns removed value or null if invalid index.
   - `get(index)` - get value at index. Returns value or null if invalid index.
   - `indexOf(value)` - get first index of value. Returns -1 if not found.
   - `contains(value)` - returns true if value exists in list.
   - `toArray()` - convert list to array.
   - `fromArray(array)` - replace list contents with array values.
   - `size` (getter) - number of nodes in list.
   - `isEmpty()` - returns true if list is empty.
   - `clear()` - remove all nodes.
   - `reverse()` - reverse the list in place.
   - `forEach(callback)` - iterate over values with callback(value, index).
   - `map(callback)` - create new array with callback(value, index).
   - `filter(callback)` - create new array with elements that pass callback test.

3) Implement using node objects with value, next, prev properties. Maintain head and tail pointers.

4) Write tests in `tests/linkedList.test.js` covering: all operations (append, prepend, insertAt, remove, removeAt, get, indexOf, contains), edge cases (empty list, single element, invalid indices), toArray/fromArray conversion, size tracking, clear/reverse operations, iteration methods (forEach, map, filter), and performance with large datasets.

5) Export `createLinkedList` from `src/index.js` as `linkedList`.
